text: Less than three hours before a curfew was set to go into effect in Louisville, upwards of 75 state police in riot gear were lined up at the Republic Plaza parking lot—along with several military vehicles. Helicopters were also seen flying overhead. https://t.co/qhb7s9AI39

text:
In New York, protesters met in Union Square to begin a borough demonstration against police brutality and racial injustice. 

“Breonna Taylor was a hero, Breonna Taylor was an essential fucking worker,” community legal advocate Huey Freeman told the crowd. https://t.co/qhb7s9AI39
